<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="229" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,743,1023]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,816,842]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Remarks.</emphasis>
Based on male genitalia, this species seems to belong to an intriguing group of species, now assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[180,323,852,878]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[180,323,852,878]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Leucotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName authority="(Holzenthal &amp; Harris 1999)" baseAuthorityName="Holzenthal &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[450,885,852,879]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zopilote">
<emphasis box="[450,466,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[479,568,852,878]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">zopilote</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Harris, S. C." box="[582,876,852,878]" firstAuthor="Holzenthal" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" pagination="540 - 568" part="101" refId="ref15360" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Harris, S. C. (1999) The genus Costatrichia Mosely in Costa Rica, with a review of the Neotropical species (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 101 (3), 540 - 568." title="The genus Costatrichia Mosely in Costa Rica, with a review of the Neotropical species (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae)" type="journal article" year="1999">Holzenthal &amp; Harris 1999</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Santos, Takiya &amp; Nessimian 2013)" baseAuthorityName="Santos, Takiya &amp; Nessimian" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[939,1432,852,879]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falsa">
<emphasis box="[939,955,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[969,1023,852,878]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">falsa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Takiya, D. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L." box="[1038,1425,852,878]" firstAuthor="Santos" journalOrPublisher="Zoologia" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" pagination="447 - 450" part="30" refId="ref15752" refString="Santos, A. P. M., Takiya, D. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. (2013) Two new species of Costatrichia (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae: Leucotrichiinae). Zoologia, 30 (4), 447 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1984 - 46702013000400012" title="Two new species of Costatrichia (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae: Leucotrichiinae)" type="journal article" year="2013">Santos, Takiya &amp; Nessimian 2013</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Those species are very distinctive from any other 
<taxonomicName box="[703,846,888,914]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[703,846,888,914]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Leucotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, but phylogenetic analyses with morphological and molecular data strongly support this placement (
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M." box="[774,980,924,951]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Santos" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" pagination="458 - 480" part="41" refId="ref15814" refString="Santos, A. P. M., Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M. (2016) Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data. Systematic Entomology, 41, 458 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12168" title="Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data" type="journal article" year="2016">
Santos 
<emphasis box="[857,905,924,950]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Due to the similarities in male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,415,960,986]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="topora">
<emphasis box="[182,415,960,986]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Acostatrichia topora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and these two 
<taxonomicName box="[585,728,960,986]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[585,728,960,986]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Leucotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, especially the processes of segments VIII and IX, this species is formally transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[525,668,996,1022]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,668,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Leucotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
